programme.title: The 700 Club
programme.desc: The 700 Club is a daily magazine programme with news, interviews, lifestyle features and true-life stories from a Christian perspective. including powerful and dramatic testimonies of God touching peoples lives. Where does the name The 700 Club come from? When the show started to air more than 50 years ago, founder and host Pat Robertson needed to have just 700 Partners to donate $5 a month to make the programme possible. Those original 700 supporters couldnt have imagined they would start a TV show that is now seen every day in over 200 countries, impacting the nations with the Gospel of Jesus Christ!

A New York Times bestselling author, her books have helped millions of people find hope and restoration through Jesus Christ. In this series you will see her powerful preaching from her home church, as well as the crusades around the world, and intriguing interviews with a variety of guests. Be inspired and encouraged this week, with Joyce Meyer on Enjoying Everyday Life.

programme.sub-title: Help For Our Healing/A Life of Love

programme.title: Hachi: A Dogs Tale
programme.desc: A film based on one of the most treasured and heartwarming true stories ever told. Professor Parker Wilson, a distinguished scholar discovers a lost Akita puppy on his way home from work. Despite initial objections from Wilsons wife, Cate, Hachi endears himself into the Wilson family and grows to be Parkers loyal companion. As their bond grows deeper, a beautiful relationship unfolds embodying the true spirit of family and loyalty, while inspiring the hearts of an entire town.

programme.title: Jeni: Seeking the Extraordinary
programme.desc: Jeni is back on the road, visiting the amazing state of Oregon in the USA. Close friend, Casey Cole, joins her in this exciting series. Together, they go fly fishing, crabbing, white water rafting, and zip lining. During their adventure, Jeni and Casey take you to the picturesque Cannon Beach and experience the fun of an exciting rodeo. Lots of laughter and adventure, times of sharing their hearts about spiritual matters, and plenty of the extraordinary.

programme.title: Holy Moly
programme.desc: Holy Moly turns the Bible into a living, breathing colouring book that will delight children of all ages. Eyes will be fixed on the screen, observing how God is at work in the story when colour is introduced to an otherwise black-and-white world. Rather than dialogue, the series focuses on the Biblical characters actions and emotions to help audiences of any language or background immediately relate to and remember these enriching stories.

programme.title: Elevation Experience

programme.title: Faith Runs Deep
programme.desc: Faith Runs Deep is the new series from the producers of the award-winning program, Jesus the Game Changer. Host Karl Faase travels around Australia, discovering the rich and inspiring history of faith Down Under, demonstrating the depth of influence of the Gospel message on Australia. The team drives from the cities to the outback in an iconic Holden ute, unearthing stories from history and today of people whose lives have been changed by Jesus, and who have deeply influenced this nation. Each episode covers a different theme or time in Australias history. Hear from historians and academics; remarkable Australians of faith; and Karl and Jane Faase about their own journey of faith.

programme.title: Drive Thru History: Ends of the Earth
programme.desc: Hosted by historian and filmmaker Dave Stotts, Drive Thru History: Ends of the Earth takes viewers on a 19-episode, global trek to every corner of the earth, to show how God has used ordinary people throughout history to take His saving grace to every nation and people.

programme.title: Bible Land Passages
programme.desc: Bible Land Passages is designed help others better understand and appreciate the Bible. Read about places like Beersheba, Jericho, Jerusalem, Caesarea, and cities surrounding the Sea of Galilee, and discover that those places exist just as the Bible describes. Explore the lands of the Bible and uncover a window into the ancient past. Sift through the archaeological data, travel down the pathways of the Bible lands and traverse through the passages of its ancient cities, trade routes, and caves and understand and appreciate the challenges of life faced by Christian forbearers, and learn how God used the historical and geographic setting of the Bible lands to refine and develop their faith. Those same real places and same real settings - when examined in the modern era - can likewise become a passage for developing greater faith and devotion for God.

He holds a BA in Theology, MA in Ancient History and Archaeology, and M in Divinity. As an internationally-acclaimed speaker and TV presenter, he has spoken and produced numerous documentaries on subjects including the Bible, Bible prophecy, world events, historical places and natural health. His passion is to share the good news of Jesus soon return.

programme.desc: When a business is starting out, its not strange that all decisions need to be made by the key business leader - often theyre the only one in the business. However, if this continues as the business grows, that leader will find themselves feeling tired, lonely and without hope. Peter talks with Kent Medwin about the idea of servant leadership - where a leader is proactively working to empower the success of the team as it grows. Kent shares how without this approach, where instead the leader holds onto making all decisions, they become a significant barrier to success. Peter and the team unpack the value that decentralised decision making creates a culture of empowerment and whilst it can be slow to get started, slow is smooth, and smooth is fast.

In fact, PowerPoint can be seen or heard by a potential audience of millions of television viewers and radio listeners across the United States, the United Kingdom, Australia, South Africa, Iran, Russia, Israel and more. Groups like the team at Be That are looking to change this, encouraging Australians to connect face to face and begin real conversations. The Be That TV Show, created in partnership with ACCTV, shares the real stories of individuals, couples and families who have journeyed through bondage to freedom and inspire others that they too can overcome challenges. Topics are discussed with host Jo Bouris, and regular panellist, Clinical Psychologist, Sarah Harriott. Guests are welcomed to the couch, who speak hope, life and encouragement through their personal experience. Viewers can then access the topic resources and corresponding questions to start their own journey to understanding and healing: Be that person they were designed to be.

programme.title: A Place in the Sun

programme.title: A Place in the Sun
programme.desc: Retired couple Dabi and Devi cant wait to bid goodbye to the grey skies of Croydon and say hello to the sunshine and heat in the seaside town of Gandia in Valencia.

programme.title: A Place in the Sun
programme.desc: Lee Juggurnauth is house hunting with Albert and Susan around Benalmadena on Spains Costa del Sol, showing them five properties for their 190,000-pound budget.

programme.title: A Place in the Sun

programme.title: Love It or List It
programme.desc: When a house no longer feels like home, homeowners are left with a big financial and emotional question: renovate or real estate? This program helps fed-up homeowners decide.

programme.title: My Lottery Dream Home
programme.desc: A dedicated wife, mother and lottery player with a daily scratchie ritual is finally rewarded. Her $1 million win has her family looking for a dream home in Western Massachusetts.

programme.title: Cyberstalker
programme.desc: Thirteen years ago, Aidens world was torn apart after an online stalker followed her into the real world and broke into her home to claim the object of his desire. The resulting night of terror ended with the murders of both Aidens mother and father. The stalker escaped the scene without Aiden seeing his face; he is gone without a trace, an unknown man, a murderer now watching Aidens every move. To escape this danger Aiden spends the next 13 years offline, in therapy and secluded anonymity. Who should Aiden trust in a web of deception where no one may be who they seem? There is nowhere for Aiden to hide when someone wants to love her to death. Mischa Barton, Dan Levy and Ron Lea star. (2012)

programme.title: The Perfect Teacher
programme.desc: When spoiled, beautiful high-schooler Devon sets her sights on her handsome teacher, she wont take no for an answer.

programme.title: Blonde and Blonder
programme.desc: When two dim-witted blonde bombshells are mistaken for the underworlds most cunning assassins, they are approached with a lucrative contract to take out the head of the Chinese mafia in a globetrotting, air-headed comedy. Two fair-haired beauties have just witnessed a high-profile mob hit, and now the Godfather is convinced that they have what it takes to rub out his most fearsome rival. After accepting a hearty payout and agreeing to carry out the dangerous assignment, the two brainless beauties hit the open road on the adventure of a lifetime.

programme.title: Michael Jackson: Searching for Neverland
programme.desc: Based on Bill and Javons book Remember the Time: The Last Days of Michael Jackson, this movie will chronicle those intimate moments between Jackson and his children, document the professional turbulence that engulfed Jackson in financial trouble and forced him back to rehearsals for the ill-fated This Is It tour that led to his early death, and help answer the question that fans around the world want to know: What really happened to the King of Pop?

programme.title: I Was Octomom
programme.desc: In 2009, Natalie Suleman gives birth to eight children with the help of IVF, only to have her life torn apart, and her identity rebranded by the media.

programme.title: Nightmare School Moms
programme.desc: Two mothers battle to see which of their overachieving daughters will be accepted to a prestigious university. However, when one of their methods quickly spirals out of control, the games turn deadly.

programme.title: A Model Murder
programme.desc: Model Kara Woods begins to get disturbing messages from one of her fans, causing her to seek help from a security influencer. Things are fine until Karas stalker shows up in person.

programme.title: Murder at the Derby
programme.desc: Kara lands her dream job at a prestigious horse stable under Jennifers mentorship, but tensions rise when Jennifers jealous brother puts everyones lives at risk.

programme.title: Happy Face Killer
programme.desc: Grisly serial killer Keith Hunter Jesperson taunts authorities with scribbled confessions bearing a smiley face at the scenes of his crimes. Based on a true story.

programme.title: Waking Up To Danger
programme.desc: A young mother picks up the pieces after a horrible accident damages her memory. She soon suspects her husbands indiscretions are what caused her suffering and that her family is in danger.

programme.title: An Amish Murder
programme.desc: A woman returns to the Amish farming community of her youth, but her peace is shattered when a murder investigation exposes a dark secret that could destroy her.

programme.title: Framed by My Husband
programme.desc: When Junes wealthy husband Rick becomes the target of an extortionist who claims he sexually assaulted her, Rick convinces his wife its an act of revenge by a spurned suitor, and enlists her help to prevent the accusations from going public. June agrees to help him pay off the extortionist, but when the woman is found dead, June becomes the prime suspect.

programme.title: Who Is Killing The Cheerleaders?
programme.desc: Ellie, a former cheerleader, returns to her high school as a teacher ten years after she was nearly killed in a series of brutal slayings on the squad. When the attacks start up again shortly after her arrival, she must find the killer before they get to her first.

programme.title: Man with my Husbands Face
programme.desc: When a womans husband disappears during a kayak trip, everyone assumes that he drowned. When she catches a glimpse of a man who looks exactly like him, it sets off a chain of events.

programme.title: Its Beginning to Look a Lot Like Murder
programme.desc: In the middle of preparing for her business biggest season, Diana Hart learns she inherited an old house from her beloved aunt who was murdered.

programme.title: The Night Stalker
programme.desc: Known to many as the "Night Stalker", Richard Ramirez was a cruel and prolific serial killer who murdered 14 people and terrorized Los Angeles in the summer of 1985. This film tells the story of Kit (Bellamy Young), an attorney who travels to San Quentin on an impossible mission to clear the name of Harrison Johnson (Hawthorne James), a death row inmate in Texas whom she believes has been wrongly accused of murders perpetrated by Ramirez (Lou Diamond Phillips). Kit lived in Los Angeles during the fear-tinged summer where Ramirez terrified its citizens and confronting him dredges up old and frightening memories of her own past. As the days count down to the Texas mans execution, Kit confronts Ramirez about his unspeakable crimes in search of an elusive confession, plunging into intense psychological depths in her quest for the truth.

programme.title: Ill Be Watching
programme.desc: Based on the novel The Purple Rose by Christi R. Walsh. After narrowly escaping the clutches of a deadly stalker, a beautiful young woman flees to a remote anonymous town, where she rebuilds her life and finds the man of her dreams, until the man of her nightmares tracks her down.

programme.title: Girl in the Box
programme.desc: In 1977, 22-year-old Colleen Stan doesnt think twice when she hitch hikes and is picked up by a young couple, Cameron and Janice Hooker. But the life she knows is completely ripped away when the couple abducts her and takes her to their home where Cameron tortures and sexually abuses her. For the next seven years, Colleen is imprisoned for up to 23 hours a day, in a coffin-sized box hidden beneath the couples bed. When not incarcerated, Colleen is part of a strange new life as a live-in slave, babysitter, and victim of Camerons bizarre and extreme sexual fantasies.

programme.title: Kidnapping in the Grand Canyon
programme.desc: When two best friends hiking the Grand Canyon trust an experienced hiking guide to bring them on an off trail adventure, things go south when he takes them captive, and they have to fight both man and nature to make it out.

programme.title: Secrets In The Desert
programme.desc: While on a road trip through the desert, Charlie and her boyfriend Aidan break down in the middle of nowhere. While Aidan waits for a tow truck, Charlie heads to a nearby diner to find help. When Aidan goes missing, Charlie finds herself stranded in a strange town unsure who to trust. The only thing she knows is she might just be their only chance to get out alive.

programme.title: Harry and Meghan: Escaping the Palace
programme.desc: The couple decide to step back from the duties of the British monarchy following the birth of their son Archie.

programme.title: Stalked by a Prince
programme.desc: Publicist Alyssa Banks thinks shes in a fairytale when she meets a British prince who whisks her away to Europe. Alyssas dream turns into a nightmare when the prince refuses to let her leave.

programme.title: Liz and Dick
programme.desc: A chronicle of the fiery, legendary, on-again off-again romance between Hollywood stars Elizabeth Taylor and Richard Burton.

programme.title: Murder Below Deck
programme.desc: When Lauren gives up the corporate life and a cheating boyfriend, she joins her best friend from college working aboard a luxury yacht in the South Pacific.

programme.title: Your Boyfriend Is Mine
programme.desc: Over the objection of his girlfriend, Ben agrees to take a job as the live-in manservant to a wealthy businesswoman, Amanda, but quickly realises he has made a deal with the devil, and has put himself and his girlfriend in mortal jeopardy.

programme.title: Petals on the Wind
programme.desc: A decade after Cathy, Christopher and Carrie escaped from their grandparents attic at Foxworth Hall, the story continues to follow the twisted plight of the family as they attempt to put their sordid past behind them, but soon discover certain secrets cant be left behind. When Cathy finds herself in an abusive relationship with a fellow dancer, Julian, Christopher and Cathy are forced to face the forbidden feelings they developed for one another while coming of age during captivity.

programme.title: Beaches
programme.desc: While remaining faithful to the original story, we follow the lifelong friendship between LA-born CC Bloom and San Francisco rich girl Hillary Whitney after they serendipitously meet on Venice Beach. In this update, CC is a budding pop star who is struggling to make it in LA until she is discovered by a music producer who helps her develop her raw talent. Hillary is the daughter of a prominent lawyer who is intent on making her own destiny and getting out from under the control of her domineering father. Their friendship - even with its ups and downs - sustains them for decades, but ends tragically with Hillarys early death.

programme.title: You Cant Take My Daughter
programme.desc: Amy Thompson is a vibrant law student in Charlotte who is attacked and raped by Demetri, a friend of a friend she met once. Discovering that she is pregnant from the rape, Amy makes the difficult decision to keep her baby, despite the fact that Demetri continues to stalk and harass her as she waits for the long-delayed trial. She gives birth to a beautiful little girl and decides to flee him and start over in Atlanta. Six years later, Demetri finds her and, to her horror, sues her for custody of her daughter. Using her own legal and investigative skills, Amy fights back.

programme.title: Expecting Amish
programme.desc: When an eventful Rumspringa leads to an unintended pregnancy, Amish teen Hannah must choose between returning to faith and family or beginning a new life elsewhere.

programme.title: V.C Andrews Pearl In The Mist
programme.desc: Fate whisked Ruby from a simple life in the Louisiana Bayou. But her new riches bring more treachery than happiness. Even after a year as a Dumas, Ruby still wonders at the splendor of the familys New Orleans mansion and rejoices in the love of the father she had never known. But true happiness in her new home is as elusive as the swamp mist. Ruby must carefully avoid her venomous stepmother, Daphne, while making every effort to befriend her twin sister, Gisselle. While attending Greenwood, the exclusive girls boarding school, Ruby doesnt lose hope in a world that never really wanted her. Ruby will have to summon every last ounce of her Cajun strength to reclaim her home, her future, and the happiness she once knew.

programme.title: Lust: A Seven Deadly Sins Story
programme.desc: Tiffanie is about to have the wedding of her dreams to her soul mate, the dashing Damon King, founder of King Enterprises. But when Damons old friend Trey arrives, fresh from prison to step in as Damons best man, Tiffanies whole world gets rocked. Sexy and mysterious, Trey triggers a passion in Tiffanie that she never expected, and suddenly the life shes always planned with Damon is uncertain. But Trey still carries wounds from his history with Damon, and his intentions toward both Tiffanie and Damon are not to be trusted.

programme.title: Girl in the Basement
programme.desc: Inspired by true events, this is the story of Sarah, a teenager imprisoned by her father in the basement of their family home for over twenty years. The father told his wife and other children that Sarah had run away to be with a boyfriend the family disapproved of. Meanwhile, as the years went by, he would secretly visit her in the basement, raping her there while her mother and siblings continued living upstairs. Sarah gave birth alone in the basement to several children. Her father let her raise one there but brought the others upstairs, claiming to his wife that Sarah has left the grandchildren on their doorstep. When Sarah finally escapes, the family learns the devastating truth about what had been going on for years right beneath their feet.

programme.title: The Beach House Murders
programme.desc: A lonely female novelist becomes a prime suspect in a homicide after a one-night tryst with a mysterious stranger who turns up dead at her summer home.

programme.title: You Better Watch Out
programme.desc: Aubreys plane is grounded due to a snowstorm, leaving her stranded for the night at a small town airport. She stumbles into the middle of a kidnapping and throws herself into danger as she tries to save the young girl stranded with them.

programme.title: V.C. Andrews Hidden Jewel
programme.desc: Rubys struggle continues to find a happy life with Beau Andreas, the true father of Pearl, and to protect their precious daughter. Sheltered from sorrow, innocent young Pearl thrives in the sunshine of a loving home, except for the haunting nightmares of her earliest years and the dark family secrets she worries will one day shadow her destiny. As Pearls journey and dreams of success swirl away with the hurricane winds, and she journeys to the swamps in search of her mother and the shocking truths of her heritage. In the warm embrace of a gentle Cajun man, she discovers a blessed refuge. But, until the storm clouds clear, Pearl cannot savour the springtime sweetness that always seems beyond tomorrow.

programme.title: Innerspace
programme.desc: A test pilot is miniaturised in a secret experiment, and accidentally injected into a hapless store clerk.

programme.title: E.T. the Extra-Terrestrial
programme.desc: While visiting the Earth at Night, a group of alien botanists is discovered and disturbed by an approaching human task force. Because of the more than hasty take-off, one of the visitors is left behind. The little alien finds himself all alone on a very strange planet. Fortunately, the extra-terrestrial soon finds a friend and emotional companion in 10-year-old Elliot, who discovered him looking for food in his familys garden shed. While E.T. slowly gets acquainted with Elliots brother Michael, his sister Gertie as well as with Earth customs, members of the task force work day and night to track down the whereabouts of Earths first visitor from Outer Space.

programme.title: Close Encounters of the Third Kind
programme.desc: Power company repairman Roy Neary witnesses unidentified flying objects in the skies near his Muncie, Indiana home. The encounter sets into action a startling chain of dramatic events. Trying desperately to understand what he has seen, Neary is increasingly driven to the emotional edge by the governmental cover up thats blocking him. With his wife struggling in vain to understand what is happening as their relationship disintegrates, Neary finds an ally in Jillian Guiler, a woman who has also witnessed nocturnal encounters and whose young son has been abducted by the alien visitors. As Roy and Jillian look for an answer to the extraordinary mystery that has engulfed them, an international team of scientists led by Claude Lacombe, a dedicated French expert on extraordinary phenomena, also pursues the truth. As Lacombe and company seek to understand the phenomenon of the skies and look for a communications break-through, their cosmic detective work reaches from the Indiana plains across the world to a remote hillside in India and then to the one place that holds the answer in an ultimate close encounter.

programme.desc: Americans Hanna and Liv are best friends backpacking in Australia. Bar owner Billy and a host of locals give the girls a riotous introduction to Down Under drinking culture but soon Hanna and Liv find themselves trapped in an unnerving situation that grows rapidly out of their control.

programme.title: River Wild

To survive the wild river, Joey will have to face her fears, and everyone will have to develop killer instincts before theyre torn apart by deception aboard the raft, or by deadly waters wreaking havoc all around them.

programme.title: The Royal Hotel
programme.desc: Americans Hanna and Liv are best friends backpacking in Australia. After they run out of money, Liv, looking for an adventure, convinces Hanna to take a temporary live-in job behind the bar of a pub called The Royal Hotel in a remote Outback mining town. Bar owner Billy and a host of locals give the girls a riotous introduction to Down Under drinking culture but soon Hanna and Liv find themselves trapped in an unnerving situation that grows rapidly out of their control.

programme.title: Tarot
programme.desc: When a group of friends recklessly violates the sacred rule of Tarot readings, they unknowingly unleash an unspeakable evil trapped within the cursed cards. One by one, they come face to face with fate and end up in a race against death.

programme.title: The Heist Before Christmas
programme.desc: A Christmas-hating boy meets two Santas in the woods, one of whom claims to have fallen from his sleigh, but he is more interested in the other man when he learns he is on the run for robbing a bank.

programme.title: If
programme.desc: A young girl who goes through a difficult experience begins to see everyones imaginary friends who have been left behind as their real-life friends have grown up.

programme.title: Dear Santa
programme.desc: A young boy who, in writing his yearly note to Santa, mixes up the letters and sends it to Satan instead.

programme.title: The Caine Mutiny Court-Martial
programme.desc: A naval officer stands trial for mutiny after taking command from a ship captain he feels is acting in an unstable way, putting in danger both the ship and its crew.

programme.title: Bob Marley: One Love
programme.desc: Celebrate the life and music of an icon who inspired generations through his message of love, peace, and unity. In this powerful and uplifting film, discover Bob Marleys incredible story of overcoming adversity and the journey behind his revolutionary music that changed the world.

programme.title: High and Low - John Galliano
programme.desc: Director Kevin Macdonald examines fashion designer John Gallianos rapid ascent, fall from grace after an antisemitic tirade, and rehabilitation.

programme.title: Two Tickets to Greece
programme.desc: France. When childhood friends Magalie and Blandine cross paths after many years, they decide to finally take their dream vacation to Greece.

programme.title: Summer Camp
programme.desc: Follows Nora, Ginny, and Mary, three childhood best friends who used to spend every summer at a sleep away camp together. After years, when the opportunity to get back together for a summer camp reunion presents itself, they all seize it.

programme.title: Flight 149: Hostage of War
programme.desc: In 1990, Iraq takes the world by surprise and invades Kuwait. BA Flight 149 from London lands in Kuwait for a scheduled stop with men, women and children aboard. The plane never reaches its final destination.

programme.title: River Wild
programme.desc: Joey (Leighton Meester) fears there could be trouble ahead after her brother Gray (Taran Killam) invites Trevor (Adam Brody), a childhood friend with a troubled past, on their white water rafting adventure with two tourists. Once they become stranded in raging rapids, the thrill-seeking trip quickly turns from exciting to utterly terrifying as the rafters are trapped in a desperate fight for their lives, all while someone seems intent on sabotage to ensure shocking secrets stay buried. To survive the wild river, Joey will have to face her fears, and everyone will have to develop killer instincts before theyre torn apart by deception aboard the raft, or by deadly waters wreaking havoc all around them.

programme.title: Night Swim
programme.desc: Former baseball player Ray Waller moves into a new home with his family. But a dark secret in the homes past will unleash a malevolent force that will drag the family into the depths of terror.

programme.title: Hypnotic
programme.desc: Determined to find his missing daughter, Austin detective, Danny Rourke instead finds himself spiraling down a rabbit hole while investigating a series of reality-bending bank robberies where he will ultimately call into question his most basic assumptions about everything and everyone in his world. Aided by Diana Cruz, an unnervingly gifted psychic, Rourke simultaneously pursues and is pursued by a lethal specter, the one man he believes holds the key to finding the missing girl only to discover more than he ever bargained for.

programme.title: Smile 2
programme.desc: About to embark on a world tour, global pop sensation Skye Riley begins experiencing increasingly terrifying and inexplicable events. Overwhelmed by the escalating horrors and the pressures of fame, Skye is forced to face her past.

programme.title: Dune: Part Two
programme.desc: Dune: Part Two will explore the mythic journey of Paul Atreides as he unites with Chani and the Fremen while on a warpath of revenge against the conspirators who destroyed his family. Facing a choice between the love of his life and the fate of the known universe, he endeavors to prevent a terrible future only he can foresee.

programme.title: Harold and the Purple Crayon
programme.desc: Inside of his book, adventurous Harold can make anything come to life simply by drawing it. After he grows up and draws himself off the books pages and into the physical world, Harold finds he has a lot to learn about real life.

programme.title: The Critic
programme.desc: A powerful London theatre critic becomes entangled in a web of deceit and murder.

programme.title: Origin
programme.desc: Follows the tragedy and triumph of Pulitzer Prize winning journalist Isabel Wilkerson as she investigates a global phenomenon of epic proportions, who experiences unfathomable personal loss and love as she crosses continents and cultures to craft one of the defining American books of our time.

programme.title: Freuds Last Session
programme.desc: Freud invites iconic author C.S. Lewis to debate the existence of God, his unique relationship with his daughter, and Lewis unconventional relationship with his best friends mother.

programme.title: The Holdovers
programme.desc: A curmudgeonly instructor at a prep school is forced to remain on campus during Christmas break to babysit a handful of students with nowhere to go.

programme.title: The Three Musketeers: Dartagnan
programme.desc: France. DArtagnan arrives in Paris trying to find his attackers after being left for dead, which leads him to a real war where the future of France is at stake.

programme.title: Bloodline Detectives
programme.desc: In San Diego, 1969, 23-year-old Mary Scott is visited by a friend when she fails to show up for work. Marys body lies on her apartment floor; shes been savagely raped and strangled to death.

programme.title: Cold Blood
programme.desc: On April 13, 2006, a sleepy Pennsylvania town is rocked when a popular dentist, John Yelenic, is discovered lying in a pool of blood in his own home. Wealthy, handsome and known for his generosity, the 45-year-olds throat has been slashed, blood covers the floor and walls, and bloody footprints lead out the back door. With their resources stretched to the limit, police uncover few clues but plenty of rumours. Why would anyone want to kill the Blairsville dentist? Was the motive money or a bitter divorce? And when a state trooper becomes the prime suspect, can police be trusted to investigate one of their own?

programme.title: Ivan Milat
programme.sub-title: Sewing The Seeds Of A Serial Killer
programme.desc: Definitive, compulsive and revelatory, this is the untold true story of serial killer Ivan Robert Marko Milat.

programme.title: Million Dollar Murders
programme.desc: In 1973, Lyn White is murdered in Coogee. Despite investigations, her killer remains unknown. A $1 million reward is offered in 2018, hoping the show will uncover new leads.

programme.title: Bloodline Detectives
programme.desc: The identities of a woman and her killer are mysteries for years until genetic genealogy offers answers.

programme.title: The First 48
programme.desc: In Detroit, Officer Anthony Wright Jr is investigating the death of a man found shot behind an abandoned house. Wright learns that there has been a second shooting just minutes after the homicide, and it has been caught on tape. In Memphis, when a woman is found dead inside a house fire, sergeant Kevin Lundy, who spent over a year working in arson, is called to the scene. He discovers that the victim had been shot, and was likely killed by someone she knew. Lundy must find out who she might have been with in the hours before her murder.

programme.title: Bloodline Detectives
programme.sub-title: Stephanie Isaacson - Schoolbag In The Road
programme.desc: In Las Vegas, Nevada, on June 1st, 1989, Stephanie Isaacson sets off on her morning walk to school. She never makes it. That same evening, her familys worst fears are confirmed.

programme.title: Cold Blood
programme.desc: In Modesto, California, a young mother is brutally murdered in her home. Police find Debi Whitlocks nearly decapitated body lying in the hallway. There is blood on the walls. Her nightgown is pulled over her face and a knife lays between her legs. Even worse, her three-year-old daughter is sleeping just feet away. Except for her purse, nothing in the house is missing or out of place. Could she have known her killer? As the investigation unfolds, police zero in on two suspects - her husband who she had recently reconciled with, and her boyfriend. But with little evidence, the case goes cold for everyone - except Debi Whitlocks mother. She refuses to give up and for six years she keeps her daughters case alive in the media. The question is, can a mothers love help to track down a killer?

programme.title: Crimes That Shook Britain
programme.desc: Dr Harold Shipman is one of the Worlds biggest serial killers. In 2000 he was convicted of murdering 215 patients by lethal injection. For over 20 years this general practitioner worked under the guise of a kind, caring man of the community. Whilst fooling his family, colleagues and patients he preyed on those who trusted them the most and killed them with an injection of diamorphine. Such a trusted pillar of the community, Shipman, went unquestioned for years killing men and women in the small town of Hyde, in the UK. His cover was eventually blown when he tried to forge one victims will. The true devastation unravelled revealing the doctor to be one of the worlds biggest single serial killers of all time. Shipman never revealed his motive and committed suicide in prison in 2004. This film documents Shipmans horrendous crimes told by the people who were affected by his crimes. Danny Mellors mother was murdered by the GP. Danny and other relatives were shocked. She d been in good health just days before. Lesley Creaseys Auntie was killed by Shipman after a routine visit to her house. She appeared fit and well to neighbours just hours before. Dr Raj Patel worked across the road from Shipman countersigning death certificates for years. His detective work along with his colleagues helped bring the murderer to justice. Debbie Massey is an undertaker who worked with Shipman. Her suspicions helped to raise the alarm.

programme.desc: While on their way to a Boston maternity class, a white suburban couple is carjacked and shot in a violent inner-city neighbourhood. On the verge of death, the man calls 911, and when police arrive on the scene, he describes their assailant as an African-American male in a jogging suit. The victims are taken to hospital, and while the man, Chuck Stuart, survives, his wife Carol and their unborn child do not. Exacerbating racial tensions in the city, the case generates huge media interest and investigators are under enormous pressure to find the culprit. No physical evidence is found in the car, but when police establish a hotline, hundreds of calls come in, and two possible suspects emerge. Did the crime stem from a drug deal gone wrong? Or could there be a third suspect and a much darker motive for murder?

programme.title: Crimes That Shook Britain
programme.desc: In 1992, 25-year-old Stephanie Slater was abducted from an empty house and held for eight torturous days in a make shift coffin. Her captor was a crazed one legged man, Michael Sams. His intention was to hold her for ransom. Stephanie endured painful days and nights in the back of his grubby workshop. She was raped, tortured and made to lie in a bin for up to 23 hours a day. Her ordeal finally came to a head when Sams carried out his elaborate plot and received 175,000 pounds ransom. Police eventually tracked him down and brought him to justice. Some of the money has never been recovered. Stephanies terrifying account is told in gripping detail in this film. Her ordeal went down in history as the first ransom demand in the UK where the hostage was released.

programme.desc: It takes a long time and a very hot fire to cremate a human body and thus destroy any evidence of foul play. Police knew that a person acting alone would probably use only one weapon, so investigators searched for a couple of killers.

programme.title: Forensic Files
programme.desc: The victim had ingested a massive amount of cyanide. An unlikely clue - a flaw on a mailing envelope - exposed a murderer who was willing to kill innocent people to get the one person he wanted.

programme.desc: September 27, 1996. On a lonely stretch of Illinois highway just outside Dekatur, an abandoned car ignites the search for a vivacious and popular young mother. Investigators comb the vehicle for clues, her boyfriend makes an impassioned public plea, and her employer offers a $10,000 reward for her safe return. But two days later, local fishermen make a grisly discovery. Parcelled into a series of plastic bags, the dismembered body of 23-year-old Karyn Slover is found floating in a local lake. But after two years and no new leads, the investigation reaches a dead end. Can forensic science crack the cold case?

On the verge of death, the man calls 911, and when police arrive on the scene, he describes their assailant as an African-American male in a jogging suit. The victims are taken to hospital, and while the man, Chuck Stuart, survives, his wife Carol and their unborn child do not. Exacerbating racial tensions in the city, the case generates huge media interest and investigators are under enormous pressure to find the culprit. No physical evidence is found in the car, but when police establish a hotline, hundreds of calls come in, and two possible suspects emerge. Did the crime stem from a drug deal gone wrong? Or could there be a third suspect and a much darker motive for murder?

programme.desc: In 1992, 25-year-old Stephanie Slater was abducted from an empty house and held for eight torturous days in a make shift coffin. Her captor was a crazed one legged man, Michael Sams. His intention was to hold her for ransom. Stephanie endured painful days and nights in the back of his grubby workshop. She was raped, tortured and made to lie in a bin for up to 23 hours a day. Her ordeal finally came to a head when Sams carried out his elaborate plot and received 175,000 pounds ransom. Police eventually tracked him down and brought him to justice. Some of the money has never been recovered. Stephanies terrifying account is told in gripping detail in this film. Her ordeal went down in history as the first ransom demand in the UK where the hostage was released.

programme.desc: September 27, 1996. On a lonely stretch of Illinois highway just outside Dekatur, an abandoned car ignites the search for a vivacious and popular young mother. Investigators comb the vehicle for clues, her boyfriend makes an impassioned public plea, and her employer offers a $10,000 reward for her safe return. But two days later, local fishermen make a grisly discovery. Parcelled into a series of plastic bags, the dismembered body of 23-year-old Karyn Slover is found floating in a local lake. An autopsy later reveals she also suffered multiple gunshot wounds to the head. At first, police have two suspects in their sights: Karyns boyfriend and her ex-husband. But after two years and no new leads, the investigation reaches a dead end. Can forensic science crack the cold case?

programme.title: Rise Of The Dictators
programme.desc: Rise of the Dictators is the story of Adolf Hitler, Benito Mussolini, and Josef Stalin; but also reveals those strong men, autocrats, and despots that followed in their footsteps.

programme.title: Rise of the Nazis
programme.desc: A look at how Hitler and the Nazi party rose to power in Germany during the 1930s. It is a powerful portrait of the greed, manipulation and frightening underestimation of Hitlers ambition.

programme.title: How the Nazis Lost the War
programme.desc: Germanys allies leading into WWII were limited to a few despots and dictators. But all of these relationships were doomed from the start and Germanys choice of strange bedfellows would come back to haunt them and they would ultimately pay a high price for those decisions.

programme.title: Line of Fire
programme.desc: The story of the siege at the great Greek city in eastern Sicily which ended the period of prosperity it had enjoyed through it agriculture and trade. Superbly chronicled by the historian Thucydides, the siege was prosecuted by the Sparta during the Peloponnesian War and was a crucial event in ancient history, for it eventually led to the downfall of Athens itself.

programme.title: Dogfights
programme.desc: In the skies above North Korea, a new kind of air war is raging at 800km/h: jet versus jet dogfighting for the first time in history.

programme.title: Secrets of World War II
programme.desc: Americas answer to fighting behind Japanese lines in the jungle was to deploy a group of highly trained fighters called Merrills Marauders.

programme.title: History of Warfare
programme.desc: The battle of Gettysburg was the turning point of the American Civil War. At the end of three days of ferocious fighting, all hopes of overall victory for the Confederacy had disappeared. But the Union triumph came at a terrible price, for their losses all but matched those of the Confederates. Names such as the Peach Orchard, Little Round Top and Cemetery Ridge wrote themselves large in American folklore, and the dreadful bloodshed of July 1-3, 1863, has never been forgotten.

programme.title: Power and Glory of The Habsburgs
programme.desc: This series traces the historical sites tied to the illustrious House of Habsburg-Lorraine, offering a fresh perspective on an 800-year legacy that shaped Europes history.

programme.title: Royals, British Aristocracy and the Nazis
programme.desc: The British royal family has always been a symbol of Nazi resistance. However, time and again, information from different sources has surfaced about the Windsors secret sympathy for the Nazi regime. The newest finds have even fuelled the suspicion that, in the summer of 1940, the abdicated King Edward VIII may have leaked sensitive war-related information to Hitlers regime with the hopes of securing their support for his plans to re assume the throne.

programme.title: History Uncovered
programme.sub-title: Sub-Primes: Blame it on the USA?
programme.desc: The subprime crisis has gone down in history as an American disaster. And yet. The shock wave hit the Old Continent hard. By revealing the fault lines in the Eurozone, it triggered the worst recession in its history and jeopardized its fragile union. At the end of the day, although the United States got back on the path to growth fairly quickly, Europe is still picking up the pieces today.

programme.desc: The story of the Universal Ruler - the man who succeeded his chieftain father at age 13 and had to struggle to overcome hostile tribes. A remarkable administrator and ruler, Genghis Khans system of khanites- the means by which he ruled conquered lands - lasted for more than 400 years after his death.

programme.title: History of Warfare
programme.desc: The Battle of Borodino took place during the Emperor Napoleons disastrous Russian invasion of 1812 and was one of the most crucial battles of the entire Napoleonic era. The two sides met just 95km from Moscow, on September 7, 1812. For a man who had earned a reputation as a military genius, Napoleon failed to make the most of his long-awaited opportunity. He simply hurled his troops at the determined Russians. The result was the single biggest bloodbath of the Napoleonic wars - more than 68,000 troops were killed or wounded.

programme.title: How the Nazis Lost the War

programme.title: Line of Fire
programme.desc: The story of the siege at the great Greek city in eastern Sicily which ended the period of prosperity it had enjoyed through it agriculture and trade. programme.title: History of Warfare
programme.desc: The battle of Gettysburg was the turning point of the American Civil War. At the end of three days of ferocious fighting, all hopes of overall victory for the Confederacy had disappeared. Names such as the Peach Orchard, Little Round Top and Cemetery Ridge wrote themselves large in American folklore, and the dreadful bloodshed of July 1-3, 1863, has never been forgotten.

programme.desc: The British royal family has always been a symbol of Nazi resistance. programme.title: Monster-In-Law
programme.desc: After years of looking for Mr. Right, Charlotte Charlie Cantilini finally finds the man of her dreams only to discover that his mother, Viola, is the woman of her nightmares. A recently-fired national news anchor who is afraid she will lose her son the way she has just lost her career, Viola does everything she can to scare off her sons new fiance by becoming the worlds worst mother-in-law. While Violas long-time assistant Ruby does her best to help Viola execute her crazy schemes, Charlie decides to fight back and the gloves come off as the women battle it out to see just who the alpha-female is.

programme.title: Honey: Rise Up And Dance
programme.desc: Aspiring street dancer Skyler is at a major crossroads in her life. Shes decided to try out for the same dance crew as her formally trained sister Tosha in order to compete for a college scholarship, but is discouraged by her family and boyfriend who doubt that her raw, edgy talent is enough for her to win. Determined to prove them all wrong, Skyler practices non-stop in Atlantas underground dance scene and catches the eye of Tyrell. He helps her take her sexy dance and hip-hop battle skills to the next level in order to achieve her dreams.

programme.title: Life Without Dick
programme.desc: In this dark romantic comedy Colleen Gibson, heir to the Rose Red Grapefruit fortune, whose cheating boyfriend Dick is coincidently taken out before singing hitman Daniel has a chance to do the job himself. When Daniel and Colleen meet, sparks fly and Daniel soon discovers that his potential new girlfriend is a much better killer than he is.

programme.title: This Is Where I Leave You
programme.desc: When their father dies, four grown siblings, bruised and banged up by their respective adult lives, are forced to return to their childhood home and live under the same roof together for a week.

programme.title: The First Wives Club
programme.desc: Join Diane Keaton, Bette Midler and Goldie Hawn in this sinfully satisfying revenge romp about a trio of first wives who team up to teach their lying, cheating ex-husbands a lesson. Ivana Trumps galvanising cameo - dont get mad, dahlinks, get everytink - sets the scene in a comedy that hinges on the self-mockery of its ageless stars. Midlers ball-busting shtick, Keatons ditsy vulnerability and Hawns eternal youth are just light-hearted grist for the mill of female friendship as a serious source of strength.

programme.desc: Vivienne, is an established singer with a successful music career, but after receiving some devastating news ahead of her upcoming world tour, she is forced to reassess her life, the decisions shes made and the relationships shes sacrificed to get there. Still reeling from the shock, she finds herself navigating the busy streets of New York City but feeling more alone than ever before. In the 24 hours that follow she must find a way to make peace with her life choices and the people she left behind including her overbearing mother, Jeanne, her long-time manager, Ben, her ex-husband, Nick and her old friend Tessa before she embarks on the next chapter of her life.
